<center>What can I compare you to, a window the sun shines through? 
Maybe the silver moon, a smile rising
The magic of the fading day, satellites on parade
A toast to the plans we've made to live like kings.

What can I compare you to, when everything looks like you? 
I get a bit confused with every Spring
Flowers that bloom your eyes, hummingbirds side by side
My heart won't stay entirely in this rib caging


oh and summer is amazing.</center>

HAPPY NEW YEAR!!!!!!

for so many reasons, this has been the best christmas i can remember. mostly just because i know it will be the last one that im with all of my friends and living at home with my family. that part is sad but atleast ive been livin it up. plus breaks not even over yet! tomorrow i leave for memphis and get to celebrate christmas two more times, with my grandparents and with my dad. and then i come back for new years! 

well, see everyone soon. and merry christmas!!!

ps look for hannah, miriam and i in todays newspaper!
break so far has been awesome. shawnee was so fun. and its almost christmas!!!!!
bday boy! this one was a messup but funny anyways it was sooo smoky drunkass "do i look homeless?" we were making fun of these dude's pants this dude was crazy.

finally, ive submitted all (six) of my applications and i feel ten thousand times less stressed. Now that i have little to worry about college-wise, that its actually starting to feel like winter out, and that we have less than two weeks of school left until break, im even more excited for christmas and in the holiday spirit than i was before! I feel like i have so much to look forward to and i cant wait until the new year. If the second semester goes by as fast as the first one did, pretty soon we'll be enjoying spring break on the beaches of panama city and not far after that, we'll all be high school graduates.. ahhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh!

So far, this weekend has been great and so christmasy. Hanging out with hannah and miriam and a few others at abbey's was really fun. And even though i got two hours of sleep, work next morning at 8 am was suprisingly not bad at all. After work i decorated the christmas tree with my mom which has always been so nostalgic for me. Its sad jake wasnt here to help us this year. That night was pretty christmasy too. Ian and i went to fountain square for the DOWNTOWN DAZZLE where we witnessed santa and two elves repel down the side of macy's and also an awesome fireworks display. Then we went to my parents christmas party, which was kind of disappointing because this little kid, who was cute at first, wouldnt leave us alone. AND all the food was already eaten. Atleast i got to have saag and some delicious peppermint hot chocolate. These pictures dont do the fireworks justice at all...but here they are anyways.

Last month i got three traffic tickets- one for speeding 18 miles over the limit and two for driving with expired plates. I went to court today and i've been so nervous about it for the past few weeks. I thought for sure i would have to pay over 400 dollars in fines and court fees, or even get my license suspended. The judge told me that normally i would have to pay 201 dollars in court fees plus 289 dollars in fines. But, for some reason or another, he said he was only going to make me pay court fees! Then, he fucked up and made my payment ticket out for 177 dollars instead of 201. What an idiotttt. So basically, i lucked out and saved over 300 dollars and i didnt get my liscense taken away!!!! What a huge relief. i cannot believe that im so lucky. 
In other news, i love andy's mediterranean grill and baklava. and im so excited for thanksgiving! Even though i wont be able to spend it with my dad and jake, and even though my mom decided to cook a "less traditional meal" (which probably means grilled cheeses or something), im looking forward to the break from school. Thanksgiving is usually my favorite holiday and this year its probably going to suck. oh well, im sure the seigel family will have some good food i can take that day.
Well, i better get back to the 6 or something applications i have to finish....Jeez.

<lj-cut text="my conscience keeps me up at night.">

I'm counting out dollars while I limp to your brownstone.
I can just barely cover what I need to get back home.
And I know we're allowed indiscretion in our lives,
but I've been making mine count every night for a while.

I keep deleting your number and name from my cell phone,
but I call every day; that's as far as my act goes.
What you have helps me turn down the noise that I make,
but when it stops it just pokes me and keeps me awake.
My friends always warned about living cliches
but my friends aren't there when I meet you these days.
I count people and street signs from the back of your car
and then skip back excited to wherever they are.

I take risks in the stall while they talk by the bar.
I won't go back outside til my memory starts
erasing itself into something less brutal,
some beautiful bullshit I pretend to belong to.
For as long as the truth tucks itself into bed,
and the beat of my heart and the heat of my breath
keep me hopeful and distant and proud of myself,
I'll keep ringing your bell every night around twelve.

i just got back from chicago a few hours ago and it was amazinng. most of our time was spent visiting colleges (depaul, loyola, the school of the art institute of chicago, university of chicago) and shopping. and eating at really good restaurants. i loved every college we visited.. some more than others. im really thinking that going to school in chicago versus new york would be a lot easier. but who knows. thats a ways away. oh! and i got everyone postcards but i couldnt remember anyones address. so i guess ill just give them to you.. ha
i leave for memphis tomorrow early and will be there until next thursday. so ill call you when i get my phone back!!!!!! i miss everyone sooo much.
jeez ive got a lot of summer to catch up on.

you know what else will help the time go by even quicker!??! a CAR! good bye metro bus, walking, and bumming rides home from school off EVERYONE. we're mainly buying it because tims best friend is selling it and "its more reliable that way." im getting it this weekend, but who knows when ill have insurance. hopefully this weekend too. in case you were wondering its a white saturn SL 1995(?). and no, it does not have 3 doors. :(

too bad im gonna be so broke buying gas and paying insurance. i was so excited about getting a raise at work but i got raised from 6 dollars an hour to an AWESOME 6.25. today at lunch people were talking about making anywhere from 8 to 12.50. what the fuck? they probably dont have to wear smocks or deal with creepy male customers who "accidentally spilled something on their pants." i hate my job. most of the time. stephanie and paige help to make it a lot more fun. 

well anyway, im ready for a kickass weekend.. how bout you?
